title: Lance Breidenbaugh’s CV
text:
Aspiring Data Analyst | Business Finance Major | BYU-Idaho

lance@breidenbaugh.net ● 561-543-2151 ● LinkedIn




Data Analyst at BYU-Idaho Support Center | Graduating July 2025


Data analysis, Power BI dashboards, Excel automation, financial auditing, SQL-based insights



Business analytics, financial systems, data pipelines, automation, education, helping teams grow with data





July 2025
Brigham Young University – Idaho
Bachelor of Science in Business Finance
Minor: Data Science | GPA: 3.74


Data Science Programming, Intermediate Statistics, Operations Management, Financial Planning, Business Analytics, Spreadsheet Analysis, Financial & Managerial Accounting, Advanced Financial Management, Databases, Programming with Functions








Created an Excel tool using double XLOOKUPs, nested IFs, and clear instructions to assess merit raise eligibility.
Reduced evaluation time by over 50% for senior managers.





Built Power BI dashboards using Power Query and DAX to analyze internal audit trends across North America.








Sep 2024 – Present - Extracted SQL data to generate insights via Power BI dashboards. - Proposed new data strategies during a phone system migration. - Collaborated with cross-functional teams to complete data projects.



Apr 2024 – Sep 2024 - Used Power Automate and Excel macros to reduce audit time by 25%. - Managed and approved multi-million-dollar AP budgets with 100% accuracy. - Discovered $1M+ in discrepancies and led efforts to resolve them.



Jan 2024 – Apr 2024 - Graded 500+ Excel assignments covering PivotTables, VBA, XLOOKUP, and more. - Designed three new rubrics to speed up grading by 20%. - Lectured for 40 students on advanced Excel topics like macros.



Apr 2022 – Apr 2024 - Cut team escalation rate by 10% using Power BI goals and follow-ups. - Found and fixed 100+ issues in the internal database to support agent workflows.





Technical Skills
Excel, VBA, Power BI, DAX, SQL, Python, R
Certifications
QPR Certified (2024)
Eagle Scout, Boy Scouts of America (2018)
